wfweb CHANGELOG
===============

This changelog covers wfweb changes only. wfweb is a fork of wfview that adds
a built-in web interface. See https://gitlab.com/eliggett/wfview for the
upstream wfview history.


v0.2.3 (2026-03-08)
--------------------

REST API:
- New plain-HTTP REST API at /api/v1/radio/* for scripting, automation, and
  microcontroller integration (ESP32, Pico W, Arduino — no TLS required)
- In SSL mode a second HTTP listener binds the WebSocket port so curl/scripts
  can reach the API without a TLS stack
- Endpoints: frequency, mode, VFO (select/swap/equalize), PTT, meters (S/SWR/power),
  gains (AF/RF/power/squelch), RX DSP (preamp, NB, NR, AGC, auto-notch, filter
  width), TX settings (split, tuner, compressor, monitor), CW send/stop
- Full combined status via GET /api/v1/radio; CORS headers on all responses
- Fix: buffer incoming data per-socket so requests fragmented across TCP
  segments are fully reassembled before parsing

DIGI panel (FT8/FT4):
- Auto-tune to standard FT8/FT4 calling frequency when the DIGI panel is
  opened, matched by nearest VFO within 500 kHz
- Block self-QSO clicks: clicking a decode row transmitted by MY CALL is
  now a no-op

Audio:
- Fix mic audio loss after FT8 TX: FT8 completion no longer tears down the
  USB audio path when the user mic is active; mic frames are suppressed
  during TX without closing the AudioWorklet session
- Remove over-aggressive ALSA IdleState watchdog that dropped mic frames
  after any buffer underrun; ALSA's own snd_pcm_recover handles transients
- MIC OFF overlay is now a persistent MIC ON/OFF toggle button

Documentation:
- REST_API.md: full endpoint reference with curl examples, response schemas,
  port table, and shell scripting recipes


v0.2.2 (2026-03-03)
--------------------

DIGI panel (FT8/FT4):
- Fix TX double-fire regression: user-initiated TX uses a 13 s slot window
  while auto re-arm reverts to 4.5 s, preventing the same slot firing twice
- Fix TX waterfall splatter and add local TX audio monitor
- Fix auto-QSO cycle, TX slot-window logic, and QSO logging state machine

Audio:
- Fix ALSA underruns during FT8 TX (USB audio path): server-side pre-buffer
  accumulates PCM chunks until the ALSA buffer is full before starting
  playback; IdleState watchdog stops the device cleanly when the buffer
  drains at end of TX, eliminating snd_pcm_recover underruns

Infrastructure:
- ft8ts submodule updated to v0.0.12; upstream ships the pack28 fix
  (short callsigns like K1FM no longer corrupted); local vendored patch removed
- CI: overwrite release assets on re-tag


v0.2.1 (2026-03-02)
--------------------

Infrastructure:
- ft8ts: vendor patched dist locally pending upstream fix for issue #1
  (pack28 bug corrupting 4-character callsigns like K1FM)
- README: FT8 screenshot, vertical mobile screenshots, CW/FT8 feature rows


v0.2.0 (2026-03-01)
--------------------

DIGI panel (FT8/FT4):
- Fix marker/signal alignment: markers now point to the visual centre of the
  tone span rather than tone 0, correcting a ~12 Hz low bias
- TX waterfall loopback: the transmitted signal is now visible in the DIGI
  waterfall during TX (locally generated samples fed into the FFT pipeline)
- QSO logged indicator: a green confirmation row is appended to the Directed
  panel whenever a QSO is logged (manually or automatically)
- Version string: console log now shows "WFWEB" with the server version
  received at connect time; hardcoded date/version string removed
- Waterfall frequency range: display now spans 300-2800 Hz (was 0-3000 Hz),
  with matching scale labels, input bounds, FFT bin mapping, and click handler
- Layout: Directed and QSO Messages columns merged into a single right column
- Mobile: long-press (500 ms) on a decode row triggers the same action as
  double-click on desktop; haptic feedback via navigator.vibrate(40)
- CQ calling controls added; double-click arm supported in QSO Messages panel
- Decoded frames sorted by decreasing SNR within each slot
- Web Worker used for FT8/FT4 decode to keep the UI thread responsive
- Waterfall frequency labels; TX/RX UX and QSO state machine fixes
- RX frequency control; smarter row-click handling; auto-desist on busy DX
- Panel rationalization; FT8/USB-only enforcement; deferred TX re-arm fix
- Mobile UI tweaks: no waterfall callsigns on small screens, stacked CQ
  buttons, message-only decode rows

Web UI:
- Panel rationalization and layout cleanup


v0.1.1 (2026-02-22)
--------------------

Packaging and stability:
- Audio error banner with actionable message shown on connection failure
- Dynamic splash screen shows the actual version string at runtime
- Fix USB audio device discovery in headless/ALSA mode
- Bake IC-7300 defaults into the binary so the app works out of the box
  without a config file (Manufacturer=0, RigCIVuInt=148, SerialPortRadio=auto,
  SerialPortBaud=115200)
- Trim audio error message to remove misleading suggestion
- .deb package: fix missing librtaudio6 dependency; add postinst script for
  systemd daemon-reload; fix YAML syntax in CI workflow
- systemd template unit file added; audio config docs clarified
- GitHub Actions CI: Linux x86_64 and ARM64 builds with .deb artifact upload


v0.1.0 (2026-02-21)
--------------------

Initial wfweb release, forked from wfview upstream (master, April 2023).

Web interface:
- Built-in HTTP/WebSocket server (HTTPS, self-signed certificate generated by
  openssl on first launch); default port 8080
- Browser-based radio control: frequency (dual VFO), mode, PTT, RF/AF/SQL gain
- Real-time S-meter, SWR, and power meter display
- RX audio streaming: server decodes rig codec to PCM Int16 LE, delivered as
  binary WebSocket frames; browser AudioWorklet with ring buffer and pre-buffer
- TX audio streaming: browser microphone via getUserMedia() to AudioWorklet to
  Int16 PCM to WebSocket to USB audio output or LAN TX path
- Mobile-responsive UI
- Headless operation: run without a display using QT_QPA_PLATFORM=offscreen

CW:
- CW transmission interface with macro buttons
- Toggle-behaviour keying; mobile gesture support; TX audio tail fix
- CW decoder using ggmorse (Goertzel algorithm); replaces earlier deep-learning
  attempt; decoder waterfall display; frequency alignment fix
- Mobile-responsive DECODE button and callsign detection

FT8/FT4 DIGI panel (initial):
- UTC-aligned 15 s / 7.5 s RX slot windows
- 4x decimation to 12 kHz; decoded with ft8ts ES module (WebAssembly)
- Band selector with standard calling frequencies (160 m - 6 m)
- All / Directed decode panels; Enable TX / Halt TX / Log QSO / Erase buttons
- Settings modal for MY CALL / MY GRID
- pack28 bug in ft8ts.mjs patched: 4-character callsigns were corrupted

Infrastructure:
- Rebranded to wfweb; headless operation documented
- ggmorse LICENSE file added
- openssl documented as a runtime dependency
- README: HTTPS/self-signed certificate noted; screenshots added
- Regulatory disclaimer added
